There was confusion in Edepie community in Yenagoa Local Government Area of Bayelsa State yesterday as a 39-year-old father of four poisoned himself and died. Neighbours said the Kogi-born Femi David Otura, was a truck driver, whose widow was nursing a two-day-old baby. His wife, Ovieizibe and four children were said to have been away from home when he killed himself. The spokesman of the state police command, Asinim Butswat, said the incident had not been reported to the command. Gunmen kidnap senator’s mother in Bayelsa Group petitions police over killing of 19-year-old girl Bayelsa: Mother of Sylva’s running mate abducted